Global estimate is special location reserved for species-level traits. Such traits include individual-level traits that do not vary among individuals of a species over ecological time-scales (e.g., sexual system), as well as emergent characteristics of individuals within a species (such as geographical range size and greatest depth observed). Species-level traits do not have contextual traits because, by definition, they apply to all individuals, globally.
